This solution works by taking the logarithm base 10 of the input number, then dividing by the logarithm base 10 of 3. If the number is a power of 3, the result will be an integer, because log(a^b) = b*log(a). Therefore, we check if the result is an integer.

If you want to solve this problem without loops/recursion, you can use a while loop to repeatedly divide the number by 3 until it becomes 1. If at any point the remainder is not 0, or the number becomes 0 before it becomes 1, then the number is not a power of three.

